value.title: Race tightening but Biden remains on top 50 days out from election
value.excerpt: With 50 days to go until Election Day on Nov. 3, it still appears to be Joe Biden’s race to lose. But the contest between the Democratic presidential nominee and President Trump has tightened over the past month.

value.title: How For-Profit Colleges Might Fare Under Joe Biden And Kamala Harris
value.excerpt: For-profit colleges have had it made the last few years. After years of scrutiny and tougher regulation, many for-profit executives made a sigh of relief when Trump—the owner of an unaccredited for-profit college—was elected.

value.title: Mike Pence highlights law and order during Wisconsin visit
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence emphasized President Donald Trump's commitment to "law and order" during a campaign stop Monday in swing state Wisconsin about 70 miles from a city where sometimes violent protests erupted after the police shooting of Jacob Blake.

value.title: GOP chairman to release interim report on Biden probe 'in about a week'
value.excerpt: Senate Homeland Security Chairman Ron Johnson (R-Wis.) said on Monday that he will soon release an interim report from his months-long probe involving the Obama administration and Hunter Biden.

value.title: Pence cancels a plan to attend a fund-raiser hosted by QAnon supporters.
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence has called off plans to attend a fund-raiser in Bozeman, Mont., on Monday evening hosted by a couple who have shown support for QAnon, the convoluted conspiracy theory built around the notion of a deep-state cabal of Satan-worshiping pedophiles and their powerful Democratic backers.
